author: Lucy Craymer
title: Rice Prices Likely to Rise as El Niño Heats Up
text:
Dry conditions caused by the El Niño weather phenomenon and falling rice inventories will likely send prices of the grain higher in the coming months, reversing years of declines and boosting the cost of Asia’s staple food.
Rice prices have been weak since 2012 due to excess supply—particularly in major producer Thailand—and declines in the currencies of a number of major exporters. With El Niño bringing dry conditions and concerns... To Read the Full Story, Subscribe or Sign In
